Description

Minimum Qualifications:
- Must be registration eligible and become licensed within 6 months of hire.
- Must be enrolled in or accepted to an accredited School of PharmacyOR;
Graduate of an approved college of pharmacy or graduate of a foreign pharmacy who has obtained Foreign Pharmacy Graduate Examination Committee certificate for purposes of getting required intern hoursOR;
Qualified Graduate who is awaiting examination for Licensure OR;
Individual participating in a residency or fellowship program.
Position Summary: Assists in all aspects of drug distribution that do not require the professional judgment of a pharmacist. Interns function in accordance with standard, written procedures and guidelines under the supervision of a pharmacist.
